{
  "text": "The usefulness of salivary cortisol measurements for the diagnosis and prediction of the risk of the recurrence of CS has been well established [CITATION_1] . However, our data revealed that there was no correlation between changes in UFC levels and those in midnight salivary cortisol levels. In addition, measurements of only midnight salivary cortisol cannot reveal the diurnal rhythm of cortisol because it is affected by the dose and timing of metyrapone administrations. Thus, multiple measurements of salivary cortisol can be more useful than measurements of midnight salivary cortisol.",
  "correct_citation": {
